# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarArc | Scene: TheBattleForTheCapital
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah stood outside on the balcony of her room. From here, the view stretched across the castle, the city and even far out to the fields beyond."
    new "Sarah stood outside on the balcony of her room. From here, the view stretched across the castle, the city and even far out to the fields beyond."

    old "She had always loved this view, but now, it made her feel like ice ran through her chest."
    new "She had always loved this view, but now, it made her feel like ice ran through her chest."

    old "Several days had passed, and Varga's prediction had come true."
    new "Several days had passed, and Varga's prediction had come true."

    old "Hassar's army had moved fast, faster than anyone could have imagined, and they had arrived at the capital to finish a war that only just begun."
    new "Hassar's army had moved fast, faster than anyone could have imagined, and they had arrived at the capital to finish a war that only just begun."

    old "Camped outside on the hills, Sarah saw an army larger than any she had ever seen in her life."
    new "Camped outside on the hills, Sarah saw an army larger than any she had ever seen in her life."

    old "Sarah's crossed her arms around her chest. She tried to exude a confidence she knew she didn't have."
    new "Sarah's crossed her arms around her chest. She tried to exude a confidence she knew she didn't have."

    old "They had prepared, but would it be enough?"
    new "They had prepared, but would it be enough?"

    old "She didn't like the idea that her fate was now outside of her hands, and she was forced to wait like a lamb to the slaughter."
    new "She didn't like the idea that her fate was now outside of her hands, and she was forced to wait like a lamb to the slaughter."

    old "Sarah looked out over the battlefield below."
    new "Sarah looked out over the battlefield below."

    old "Atop the hillside, Hassar's army had almost finished moblizing. Their front rank extended across the entire hillside, with every man sitting atop a horse."
    new "Atop the hillside, Hassar's army had almost finished moblizing. Their front rank extended across the entire hillside, with every man sitting atop a horse."

    old "Sarah had never seen anything like this."
    new "Sarah had never seen anything like this."

    old "On their side, the walls were well fortified and rows of soldiers covered nearly every part of it."
    new "On their side, the walls were well fortified and rows of soldiers covered nearly every part of it."

    old "The archers were in position, but without the signal to fire, had kept their bows loose."
    new "The archers were in position, but without the signal to fire, had kept their bows loose."

    old "Out further in the field, Rosanna's army had taken to the center of the battlefield. Each regiment stood in perfect formation."
    new "Out further in the field, Rosanna's army had taken to the center of the battlefield. Each regiment stood in perfect formation."

    old "The flanks were covered by the heavy cavalry, most provided by Marion's family, Achillea. Their soldiers wore full-plated armor, shined so bright that the sun reflected off them."
    new "The flanks were covered by the heavy cavalry, most provided by Marion's family, Achillea. Their soldiers wore full-plated armor, shined so bright that the sun reflected off them."

    old "There was no single battalion in all of Rosanna that was more well equipped. She knew Marion was somewhere among them."
    new "There was no single battalion in all of Rosanna that was more well equipped. She knew Marion was somewhere among them."

    old "Near the center, off to the back, the banner of house Rose waved. The gold and red banner, adorned with a black rose, stood defiant."
    new "Near the center, off to the back, the banner of house Rose waved. The gold and red banner, adorned with a black rose, stood defiant."

    old "Somewhere near that banner was Thomas."
    new "Somewhere near that banner was Thomas."

    old "The idea alone made Sarah's heart feel like stopping."
    new "The idea alone made Sarah's heart feel like stopping."

    old "She had seen her brother shortly before he left for the battlefield. He had looked more like a child playing at being a soldier than a real soldier. Then again, perhaps that was what he was."
    new "She had seen her brother shortly before he left for the battlefield. He had looked more like a child playing at being a soldier than a real soldier. Then again, perhaps that was what he was."

    old "Underneath all the regalia and protocol, her brother was still a child, who had never seen a real battlefield in his life."
    new "Underneath all the regalia and protocol, her brother was still a child, who had never seen a real battlefield in his life."

    old "Sarah brought her hands together and offered up a soft prayer for the gods to hear."
    new "Sarah brought her hands together and offered up a soft prayer for the gods to hear."

    old "Above all, even above victory, she prayed for Thomas to be safe."
    new "Above all, even above victory, she prayed for Thomas to be safe."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah began to see stacks of smoke rise from Hassar's army."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah began to see stacks of smoke rise from Hassar's army."

    old "The ranks in his army began to shift and move, confusion spread through them."
    new "The ranks in his army began to shift and move, confusion spread through them."

    old "Sarah tried to make sense of it, but only after some time did she understand. The large trebuchets that had been built days before, were on fire."
    new "Sarah tried to make sense of it, but only after some time did she understand. The large trebuchets that had been built days before, were on fire."

    old "Perhaps the gods did listen to her, she wondered."
    new "Perhaps the gods did listen to her, she wondered."

    old "She watched as Hassar's army tried to put out the flames, but most burned down entirely. Those saved, were in no working order."
    new "She watched as Hassar's army tried to put out the flames, but most burned down entirely. Those saved, were in no working order."

    old "The two armies faced off for nearly an hour, neither willing to move first."
    new "The two armies faced off for nearly an hour, neither willing to move first."

    old "Hassar's army, now without any artillery, was trying to adapt their strategy."
    new "Hassar's army, now without any artillery, was trying to adapt their strategy."

    old "Suddenly, movements on the battlements drew Sarah's attention."
    new "Suddenly, movements on the battlements drew Sarah's attention."

    old "Varga had issued the order to fire a first volley of arrows. In unison, all of the archers atop the wall drew back their bows and released a wave of arrows."
    new "Varga had issued the order to fire a first volley of arrows. In unison, all of the archers atop the wall drew back their bows and released a wave of arrows."

    old "From so far away, the arrows seemed to fly slowly, but when they rained down on Hassar's army, Sarah could see the destruction they caused."
    new "From so far away, the arrows seemed to fly slowly, but when they rained down on Hassar's army, Sarah could see the destruction they caused."

    old "Soldiers collapsed, some from the arrows, others because the line began to break as soldiers tried to dodge the rain of arrows."
    new "Soldiers collapsed, some from the arrows, others because the line began to break as soldiers tried to dodge the rain of arrows."

    old "Not soon had the first wave landed, when a second one quickly followed."
    new "Not soon had the first wave landed, when a second one quickly followed."

    old "The damage seemed only amplified. The chaos now spread further, deeper into Hassar's army, as discipline began to fracture."
    new "The damage seemed only amplified. The chaos now spread further, deeper into Hassar's army, as discipline began to fracture."

    old "Sarah understood what Hassar did, they could not remain in their current position."
    new "Sarah understood what Hassar did, they could not remain in their current position."

    old "A loud battle horn rang out over the battlefield, and as if suddenly recovering all their training, Hassar's army began to move forward as one."
    new "A loud battle horn rang out over the battlefield, and as if suddenly recovering all their training, Hassar's army began to move forward as one."

    old "His army charged down the hill, the momentum causing the soldiers and their horses to move at an incredible speed."
    new "His army charged down the hill, the momentum causing the soldiers and their horses to move at an incredible speed."

    old "So massive was the charge, that Sarah saw a cloud of dust thrown up so large it blocked part of the battle."
    new "So massive was the charge, that Sarah saw a cloud of dust thrown up so large it blocked part of the battle."

    old "But she could still see the moment Hassar's vanguard clashed against Rosanna's frontline."
    new "But she could still see the moment Hassar's vanguard clashed against Rosanna's frontline."

    old "It was what Hassar had wanted to avoid, and exactly what Thomas had hoped for. Hassar's cavalry drove straight into a fortified front line, lined with pikes designed to counter the cavalry charge."
    new "It was what Hassar had wanted to avoid, and exactly what Thomas had hoped for. Hassar's cavalry drove straight into a fortified front line, lined with pikes designed to counter the cavalry charge."

    old "Sarah watched as countless soldiers and their horses had their momentum crushed to a halt, the row of pikes being raised up to stab upwards, knocking soldiers off their mounts, or stabbing the horses in the neck."
    new "Sarah watched as countless soldiers and their horses had their momentum crushed to a halt, the row of pikes being raised up to stab upwards, knocking soldiers off their mounts, or stabbing the horses in the neck."

    old "In mere moments, the entire charge had been brought to a halt, crushed on the iron frontline."
    new "In mere moments, the entire charge had been brought to a halt, crushed on the iron frontline."

    old "Now, in front of the Rosannan army, the battlefield turned into a slaughter house."
    new "Now, in front of the Rosannan army, the battlefield turned into a slaughter house."

    old "Unable to break their charge, the following waves of cavalry crashed atop the first wave, with one wave burrying the next."
    new "Unable to break their charge, the following waves of cavalry crashed atop the first wave, with one wave burrying the next."

    old "Out ahead of the front line, the field turned into a nightmarish mix of body parts of horses and men, crawling through one another, crushing, drowning, breaking."
    new "Out ahead of the front line, the field turned into a nightmarish mix of body parts of horses and men, crawling through one another, crushing, drowning, breaking."

    old "As another horn roared out, Rosanna's battle horn, the front line began to move forward."
    new "As another horn roared out, Rosanna's battle horn, the front line began to move forward."

    old "Spears were switched for short blades, as the soldiers began to move forward, into the collapsing army of Hassar."
    new "Spears were switched for short blades, as the soldiers began to move forward, into the collapsing army of Hassar."

    old "It was not so much a battle as it was a slaughter. Soldiers found the enemy trapped under their horses, and jabbed their blades into their necks, killing the enemy with ease."
    new "It was not so much a battle as it was a slaughter. Soldiers found the enemy trapped under their horses, and jabbed their blades into their necks, killing the enemy with ease."

    old "They died without in great numbers and with little glory."
    new "They died without in great numbers and with little glory."

    old "Rosanna's army swarmed forward, each soldier hungrily looking for an easy kill to boast about."
    new "Rosanna's army swarmed forward, each soldier hungrily looking for an easy kill to boast about."

    old "Further in the back, Sarah saw Hassar's army beginning to regroup."
    new "Further in the back, Sarah saw Hassar's army beginning to regroup."

    old "The vanguard had been wiped out, but the later waves, having seen the strategic disaster, were able to abort their attack."
    new "The vanguard had been wiped out, but the later waves, having seen the strategic disaster, were able to abort their attack."

    old "As they tried to regroup, Varga and his archers kept up the pressure, releasing wave after wave of arrows with deadly accuracy."
    new "As they tried to regroup, Varga and his archers kept up the pressure, releasing wave after wave of arrows with deadly accuracy."

    old "Hassar's army split in two, each half rushing around the front line, hoping to circle around the pike wall."
    new "Hassar's army split in two, each half rushing around the front line, hoping to circle around the pike wall."

    old "Hassar's cavalry was fast, and easily outran the infantry, but on the flanks they discovered Rosanna's heavy cavalry."
    new "Hassar's cavalry was fast, and easily outran the infantry, but on the flanks they discovered Rosanna's heavy cavalry."

    old "Unable to outrun those, Hassar's troops found themselves quickly bogged down in a frenzied melee as the heavy cavalry closed the distance."
    new "Unable to outrun those, Hassar's troops found themselves quickly bogged down in a frenzied melee as the heavy cavalry closed the distance."

    old "With the advantage of their speed lost, they now suffered the disadvantage of their light armor. Their weapons found no purchase against the plate armor of the heavy cavalry units."
    new "With the advantage of their speed lost, they now suffered the disadvantage of their light armor. Their weapons found no purchase against the plate armor of the heavy cavalry units."

    old "Trapped in a slog of a fight, Rosanna's infantry began to close in on Hassar's troops. On the outer edges, some horsemen were already beginning to be dragged down from their horses."
    new "Trapped in a slog of a fight, Rosanna's infantry began to close in on Hassar's troops. On the outer edges, some horsemen were already beginning to be dragged down from their horses."

    old "Sarah could only just make out men being thrown into the mud and stabbed to death."
    new "Sarah could only just make out men being thrown into the mud and stabbed to death."

    old "Then, as if a lighting bolt shot through Hassar's army..."
    new "Then, as if a lighting bolt shot through Hassar's army..."

    old "It broke."
    new "It broke."

    old "On all sides, men began to ride off, wildly, in all directions."
    new "On all sides, men began to ride off, wildly, in all directions."

    old "Even Sarah, with her little experience of war, could see that this was no strategy."
    new "Even Sarah, with her little experience of war, could see that this was no strategy."

    old "Hassar's army was routing."
    new "Hassar's army was routing."

    old "Trapped down hill, the speed of their escape was limited. Many men died from an arrow to the back."
    new "Trapped down hill, the speed of their escape was limited. Many men died from an arrow to the back."

    old "Many others, too deep into the battle, only realized that their comrades had left them to die, when the Rosannan army encircled them."
    new "Many others, too deep into the battle, only realized that their comrades had left them to die, when the Rosannan army encircled them."

    old "Some fought on like lions, hoping to win some glory in their final moment, and yet others, seeing no purpose, simply dropped their weapons and waited for the end."
    new "Some fought on like lions, hoping to win some glory in their final moment, and yet others, seeing no purpose, simply dropped their weapons and waited for the end."

    old "It was a massacre."
    new "It was a massacre."

    old "By the time the dust had cleared completely, Sarah could see that one regiment of the army had rushed up the hill and was now burning the entire tribal camp to the ground."
    new "By the time the dust had cleared completely, Sarah could see that one regiment of the army had rushed up the hill and was now burning the entire tribal camp to the ground."

    old "All over, men were running away, only to find themselves ran down or caught by an arrow."
    new "All over, men were running away, only to find themselves ran down or caught by an arrow."

    old "Off in the far distance, near the horizon, scattered war groups were seen still riding as fast as they could."
    new "Off in the far distance, near the horizon, scattered war groups were seen still riding as fast as they could."

    old "As the sun began to set, the land turned an odd mix of gold and blood red."
    new "As the sun began to set, the land turned an odd mix of gold and blood red."

    old "Sarah had imagined both victory and defeat, but she still found herself surprised by how this moment made her feel."
    new "Sarah had imagined both victory and defeat, but she still found herself surprised by how this moment made her feel."

    old "A rush of excitement ran through her body, a heat, eminating from her chest, drowned out all other sensations."
    new "A rush of excitement ran through her body, a heat, eminating from her chest, drowned out all other sensations."

    old "Down below, a bloodbath, but in her heart, ecstasy."
    new "Down below, a bloodbath, but in her heart, ecstasy."

    old "She had never dared to dream that delivering this carnage to her enemies, could feel so good."
    new "She had never dared to dream that delivering this carnage to her enemies, could feel so good."

    old "As word of the victory spread through the capital, Sarah saw the citizens run out onto the street, celebrating and hailing the returning army as champions."
    new "As word of the victory spread through the capital, Sarah saw the citizens run out onto the street, celebrating and hailing the returning army as champions."

    old "Loud, above all others, she heard them sing Thomas' name."
    new "Loud, above all others, she heard them sing Thomas' name."

    old "She could finally make out a man, dressed in full kingly regalia, leading the front of the returning army."
    new "She could finally make out a man, dressed in full kingly regalia, leading the front of the returning army."

    old "Thomas. He lived."
    new "Thomas. He lived."

    old "Less primal than the earlier emotion, but closer to her heart, she felt a deep joy, knowing that her brother had survived."
    new "Less primal than the earlier emotion, but closer to her heart, she felt a deep joy, knowing that her brother had survived."

    old "Sarah left her room to go to the great hall and greet her brother."
    new "Sarah left her room to go to the great hall and greet her brother."

    old "She arrived just as the men threw open the great doors of the castle and marched in, loudly screaming."
    new "She arrived just as the men threw open the great doors of the castle and marched in, loudly screaming."

    old "My sister!"
    new "My sister!"

    old "Thomas' voiced boomed out over everyone else."
    new "Thomas' voiced boomed out over everyone else."

    old "He ran up towards Sarah and grabbed her, lifting her off her feet and spinning her around before putting her back down."
    new "He ran up towards Sarah and grabbed her, lifting her off her feet and spinning her around before putting her back down."

    old "You should have seen me Sarah!"
    new "You should have seen me Sarah!"

    old "Varga and Marion came up as well. All around them, soldiers were spilling into the castle."
    new "Varga and Marion came up as well. All around them, soldiers were spilling into the castle."

    old "The king, he fought as if posessed by the heroes of old."
    new "The king, he fought as if posessed by the heroes of old."

    old "Thomas, acting as if drunk, threw his arms around both Marion and Varga, pulling them closer."
    new "Thomas, acting as if drunk, threw his arms around both Marion and Varga, pulling them closer."

    old "Marion, Varga, you call me Thomas from now on. Enough with this king shit. We fought side by side, that makes you my equal in my book."
    new "Marion, Varga, you call me Thomas from now on. Enough with this king shit. We fought side by side, that makes you my equal in my book."

    old "Varga laughed."
    new "Varga laughed."

    old "Very well, Thomas."
    new "Very well, Thomas."

    old "Marion joined in, but seemed pained by the lack of protocol."
    new "Marion joined in, but seemed pained by the lack of protocol."

    old "Absolutely...Thomas."
    new "Absolutely...Thomas."

    old "Others came up behind Thomas, vying for his attention. Thomas threw up his hands and made a face at Sarah, as if to suggest he was powerless, and let himself be dragged into the celebratory mob."
    new "Others came up behind Thomas, vying for his attention. Thomas threw up his hands and made a face at Sarah, as if to suggest he was powerless, and let himself be dragged into the celebratory mob."

    old "Sarah saw an entirely new side of her brother."
    new "Sarah saw an entirely new side of her brother."

    old "All around her, she saw soldiers dragging one another in every direction. She knew tonight the castle wouldn't sleep."
    new "All around her, she saw soldiers dragging one another in every direction. She knew tonight the castle wouldn't sleep."

    old "Sarah watched as people began to pull Varga and Marion away."
    new "Sarah watched as people began to pull Varga and Marion away."

    old "Speak privately with Varga."
    new "Speak privately with Varga."

    old "Sarah walked up to Varga before he could be dragged away."
    new "Sarah walked up to Varga before he could be dragged away."

    old "Varga, could we speak?"
    new "Varga, could we speak?"

    old "Varga waved away the soldiers, urging them to leave him be and turned to Sarah."
    new "Varga waved away the soldiers, urging them to leave him be and turned to Sarah."

    old "Of course, Sarah."
    new "Of course, Sarah."

    old "Varga came up close to Sarah. She saw he was already holding a flagon of beer."
    new "Varga came up close to Sarah. She saw he was already holding a flagon of beer."

    old "Good that I got to you while you can still speak and stand up straight."
    new "Good that I got to you while you can still speak and stand up straight."

    old "I can hold my drink, trust me on that, Princess."
    new "I can hold my drink, trust me on that, Princess."

    old "He extended the flagon to Sarah."
    new "He extended the flagon to Sarah."

    old "A lady favors wine..."
    new "A lady favors wine..."

    old "But all I have is beer, and I've been told it's impolite to let someone drink alone."
    new "But all I have is beer, and I've been told it's impolite to let someone drink alone."

    old "Sarah smiled at Varga, took the flagon from his hands, and put it to her lips."
    new "Sarah smiled at Varga, took the flagon from his hands, and put it to her lips."

    old "Having been too worried to eat or drink much of anything before the battle, the beer quenched Sarah's thirst."
    new "Having been too worried to eat or drink much of anything before the battle, the beer quenched Sarah's thirst."

    old "She handed the flagon back to Varga."
    new "She handed the flagon back to Varga."

    old "I could get used to it."
    new "I could get used to it."

    old "And here I thought you were having a civilizing effect on me, maybe I'm uncivilizing you?"
    new "And here I thought you were having a civilizing effect on me, maybe I'm uncivilizing you?"

    old "It will take a lot more than a sip of your beer to undo the decades of protocol training."
    new "It will take a lot more than a sip of your beer to undo the decades of protocol training."

    old "I'd like to see that side one day."
    new "I'd like to see that side one day."

    old "They began to walk together, down one of the hallways, away from the celebrating masses."
    new "They began to walk together, down one of the hallways, away from the celebrating masses."

    old "Sarah considered her words for a while, before deciding to speak."
    new "Sarah considered her words for a while, before deciding to speak."

    old "Varga...you were out there today, on the battle. Tell me, honestly, how did Thomas do?"
    new "Varga...you were out there today, on the battle. Tell me, honestly, how did Thomas do?"

    old "I was commanding the battlements, but you're right, I did get a good overview of the battlefield."
    new "I was commanding the battlements, but you're right, I did get a good overview of the battlefield."

    old "Honestly, from what I saw, Thomas fought valiantly."
    new "Honestly, from what I saw, Thomas fought valiantly."

    old "He kept his calm, he didn't lose sight of the larger strategy, and when the time came, he drove as far into the melee as a king responsibly should."
    new "He kept his calm, he didn't lose sight of the larger strategy, and when the time came, he drove as far into the melee as a king responsibly should."

    old "Sarah nodded along as she listened."
    new "Sarah nodded along as she listened."

    old "If I can be so bold...I think I understand your worry, and perhaps, I even shared it. That perhaps Thomas' nature made him unsuited for war, but he was everything one could hope."
    new "If I can be so bold...I think I understand your worry, and perhaps, I even shared it. That perhaps Thomas' nature made him unsuited for war, but he was everything one could hope."

    old "And you should have seen the soldiers, they loved him. They carried him on their shoulders, chanting his name."
    new "And you should have seen the soldiers, they loved him. They carried him on their shoulders, chanting his name."

    old "Sarah had taken a few more swigs of Varga's beer, and to her surprise, felt her face glowing."
    new "Sarah had taken a few more swigs of Varga's beer, and to her surprise, felt her face glowing."

    old "This beer...where did it come from?"
    new "This beer...where did it come from?"

    old "Suddenly, Varga looked shocked."
    new "Suddenly, Varga looked shocked."

    old "Ooh, Sarah, I'm so sorry...I forgot."
    new "Ooh, Sarah, I'm so sorry...I forgot."

    old "Forgot what?"
    new "Forgot what?"

    old "Sarah heard a slight slur in her own words."
    new "Sarah heard a slight slur in her own words."

    old "Where I come from, the beer is horrid, but it's all we can afford. So in order to make it last longer, we spike it with addelroot, to get yourself drunk faster."
    new "Where I come from, the beer is horrid, but it's all we can afford. So in order to make it last longer, we spike it with addelroot, to get yourself drunk faster."

    old "Help! Help! I'm being poisoned by Lord Varga!"
    new "Help! Help! I'm being poisoned by Lord Varga!"

    old "Varga shushed her."
    new "Varga shushed her."

    old "That's not funny Sarah, they'd whip me if anyone heard you."
    new "That's not funny Sarah, they'd whip me if anyone heard you."

    old "Sarah linked her arm though Varga's arm. They kept walking down the hallway together."
    new "Sarah linked her arm though Varga's arm. They kept walking down the hallway together."

    old "Sarah joked."
    new "Sarah joked."

    old "Varga only shook his head."
    new "Varga only shook his head."

    old "Forgive me Princess, but you're a horrible drunk."
    new "Forgive me Princess, but you're a horrible drunk."

    old "Maybe the problem is that I've got a head start on you, and you need to keep up?"
    new "Maybe the problem is that I've got a head start on you, and you need to keep up?"

    old "Suddenly, Sarah realized they had wandered all the way to the door to her bedroom."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah realized they had wandered all the way to the door to her bedroom."

    old "Let's keep drinking. I have some wine in my room."
    new "Let's keep drinking. I have some wine in my room."

    old "Sarah pushed open the door to her bedroom and stood in the opening."
    new "Sarah pushed open the door to her bedroom and stood in the opening."

    old "I have some more wine in my room, come in, I'll give you a chance to catch up."
    new "I have some more wine in my room, come in, I'll give you a chance to catch up."

    old "She saw Varga doubting."
    new "She saw Varga doubting."

    old "Come in, that's an order from your sovereign."
    new "Come in, that's an order from your sovereign."

    old "He smiled at her."
    new "He smiled at her."

    old "You're not my sovereign."
    new "You're not my sovereign."

    old "I'm close enough."
    new "I'm close enough."

    old "Sarah grabbed Varga by his shirt and pulled him into the room, closing the door behind him."
    new "Sarah grabbed Varga by his shirt and pulled him into the room, closing the door behind him."

    old "Sarah walked through the room, slightly off balance, making her way to one of the wardrobes. After some searching, she fished out a bottle of wine from one of the drawers."
    new "Sarah walked through the room, slightly off balance, making her way to one of the wardrobes. After some searching, she fished out a bottle of wine from one of the drawers."

    old "Found it!"
    new "Found it!"

    old "She uncorked the bottle, put the bottle to her lips, threw back her head and drank a quick swig straight from the bottle."
    new "She uncorked the bottle, put the bottle to her lips, threw back her head and drank a quick swig straight from the bottle."

    old "Sarah handed the bottle to Varga, who was still standing close to the door, as if nailed to the floor."
    new "Sarah handed the bottle to Varga, who was still standing close to the door, as if nailed to the floor."

    old "I can be...provincial too...you know."
    new "I can be...provincial too...you know."

    old "Varga in his turn also drank straight from the bottle."
    new "Varga in his turn also drank straight from the bottle."

    old "Sarah sat down on the edge of her bed and patted the side, inviting Varga to come sit next to her."
    new "Sarah sat down on the edge of her bed and patted the side, inviting Varga to come sit next to her."

    old "Sarah...Princess...I don't know if I should be here."
    new "Sarah...Princess...I don't know if I should be here."

    old "Sarah rolled her eyes."
    new "Sarah rolled her eyes."

    old "Call me 'Princess' again and I might actually have you whipped. Sit next to me. It was impolite to let someone drink alone, right?"
    new "Call me 'Princess' again and I might actually have you whipped. Sit next to me. It was impolite to let someone drink alone, right?"

    old "Varga sighed and sat down next to Sarah on the edge of her bed."
    new "Varga sighed and sat down next to Sarah on the edge of her bed."

    old "Passing the bottle back and forth, the two quickly drank through most of the wine."
